snippet.textDisplay: Pakistan is a Land of Poets & Derveshis, Love & Romances: Among them Sohni Mahiwal, Mirza Sahiban, Heer Ranjha, Sassi Pannu, Momal Ranu.Pakistani people are extremely sensitive, loving, hospitable, and trusting.When Pakistani calls you a friend: He/She will die for you.Metaphysics of Ali Hujweri aka Hazrat Data Ganj Baksh reaches celestial realm and connects Human Spirit with the Creator of Multiverses.Sprouting from the concrete floor of a madrassa is the bark of the ancient Karir tree that has remained rooted to this spot as the world around it changed. The shade of this tree was the madrassa itself when Baba Farid Shakarganj, head of the Sufi tradition of Chistiya, moved here – a small town called Ajodhan on the banks of the Sutlej river. He wanted to be as far away from the political elite as possible. Over time, as the stature of the shrine grew, so did the city, which came to be called Pakpattan (pure ford) in honour of the saint, in Punjab province.
